 the subprime mortgage crisis goldman sachs suffered during the  financial crisis and received a  billion investment from the united states department of the treasury as part of the troubled asset relief program a financial bailout created by the emergency economic stabilization act of  the investment was made in november  and was repaid in june  the list of former employees of goldman sachs who moved on to government positions includes former us secretaries of the treasury robert rubin and henry paulson current united states secretary of the treasury steven mnuchin current chief economic advisor gary cohn european central bank president mario draghi former bank of canada governor and current governor of the bank of england mark carney and the current prime minister of australia malcolm turnbull in addition former goldman employees have headed the new york stock exchange the world bank and major banks such as citigroup and merrill lynch contents  history  –  –  –  initial public offering of goldman sachs     – subprime mortgage crisis  profiting from the  subprime mortgage crisis  creation of gsamp trust s  conversion to a bank holding company  reputation tarnished  tarp and berkshire hathaway investment   use of federal reserves emergency liquidity programs   acquisition of remainder of jbwere  shut down of global alpha hedge fund   acquisition of business from deutsche bank   apples  billion bond offering   twitter initial public offering   underwriting of grand parkway system toll revenue bond   purchase of australian loan portfolio from suncorp   setlcoin   establishment of gs bank   retirement plan technology acquisition   purchase of petróleos de venezuela bonds   current operations  investment banking  investing and lending  institutional client services  investment management  gs capital partners  corporate citizenship  goldman sachs global leaders program  climate change policies  employee contributions  goldman sachs gives  community teamworks  junior bank